                            <comment id="13945658" author="cnauroth" created="Mon, 24 Mar 2014 20:38:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m attaching a patch.  This was discovered while testing HDFS ACLs with &lt;tt&gt;dfs.client.retry.policy.enabled&lt;/tt&gt; set to &lt;tt&gt;true&lt;/tt&gt;.  Running the ls command would print a stack trace if the NameNode does not have ACLs enabled, or if the NameNode is pre-2.4 and therefore does not have the ACL RPC endpoints defined.  The same log message is logged at both debug and info level.  Retries are supposed to be transparent to the client, so it&apos;s appropriate for this logging to be at debug level, and we can remove the redundant info level log.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13945678" author="szetszwo" created="Mon, 24 Mar 2014 20:55:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 patch looks good.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
